==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Escarpment
<hw>Es*carp"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>escarpement</ets>.]</ety> <def>A steep descent or declivity; steep
face or edge of a ridge; ground about a fortified place, cut away nearly
vertically to prevent hostile approach. See <er>Scarp</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>-escent</ent>⟦br⟧
